Alright, i may be trippin' alone right now, but i just love being me!!! Thats all i can say. Hahahahahaa. Ohh man. Today i've just come to terms with myself, and i mean shiett, i'm my own best friend, right?! I've always been okay with being me, but tonight i'm way more then okay with myself and i love it! Holy shit. Thiis life is crazyyy!

Now the house is quiet as a hollow head
And I'm walking round bumping into things you said
This has not been as easy as I thought it would
I'd be cooling down the fire if I thought I could

But I'm lonely again tonight
I can feel it like a knot in my side
They keep saying this is part of the ride
But I'm not getting stronger

Yet hold me against the light
And do you see any bullet inside?
Wouldn't find one if you magnified
Because you've got the wrong girl



Yeah...

On a good note the weather has been so nice!!! It's making me so damn happy that i could shart my pants. But thats besides the point...everyone is just so much more pleasant to be around when it's warmer out and thats the bottom line. But i really need to buckle down. I received my mid-terms this past week and i'm getting two F's and a D! I'm fucking shocked, but i don't know why...i put myself in this situation and i know i wasn't doing the work. I got what i deserved. I'm just so sick of being a disappointment when it comes to school. Ever since i can recall i've gotten shitty ass grades. Everyday i tell myself that i can't keep doing this! Everyday i tell myself "tomorrows a new day, i'll do this tomorrow". Everything in my life always starts tomorrow. I need to stop being so lazy. My mom and i talked today and i just felt like such a worthless turd. Shes so right about everything. I do not take anything seriously! I think that everything is suppose to be fun and i'm suppose to be out with my friends 24/7. As much as i hate saying this, life is not one big party. I've got plans in my life that i'm determined on accomplishing. I need to wake the fuck up! Life isn't about spending every waking minute thinking about what i'm gonna go do after school or what i'm going to do this weekend. I seriously care about my friends more then anything else in my entire life...possibly more then my family. I don't know if thats bad, but it can't be all that good. I want to do so much with my life and i have so much confidence that i'm going to do good with my life and be successful when really, i do absolutely nothing to support my confidence. So once again i have waited until the last four weeks of school to try to bring up my grade as much as possible in the hopes of not having to go back to summer school. I just hope i can pull this off.

I talk to Yen last night online. Shes not doing too good. She misses everyone so much! I miss her so much. Every song on my ipod reminds me of her. Hell, i even cried in my Interactive Media lab listining to Angels and Airways- The Adventure...and she'd always make fun of that song! Its just shitty how much everyyy singlee fuckingg thingg reminds me of her. But whats so unbelievable is that it's already been 7 months since i've seen her!! It's more then half way over. I'm praying these last 6 months to go are fast ones.

Last night i was at my friends Jeremy and Chads house and we were obviously smoking and when i smoke too much THC i have really fucking bad acid flashbacks and i started to feel like my whole body was freezing over and more shit happened but i'd never be able to explain it to you guys. So i went to the bathroom to chill out because it was the closest room that i could make it to. So i sat in the bathroom for five minutes, and i started freakin out in there too. so i got up and moved across the hall and i was going to tell them that i needed to go outside but i fainted in the middle of the hallway and i was out dude. It was fucking scarey. I could hear what everyone was saying and i could talk to them, but for some reason i didn't want to talk to them, i just wanted to lay there. I seriously thought i was going to fucking die. It was an out of body experience, and it was fucking scary.
